content:
Here is the cleaned-up text:

Vlocity OmniAnalytics can track user interactions with OmniScripts and FlexCards without a third-party tag manager.

Enable OmniAnalytics and Store Tracking Data.

Prepare the OmniScripts and/or FlexCards to be tracked. See Import and Activate the Example OmniScript and Import and Activate the Example Card.

Create a Tracking Group and Add Components to Track. Specify the example OmniScript and Card as components to be tracked.

Create a Lightning App Page with a Tracking Manager. This page includes the example OmniScript and Card and the Vlocity Tracking Manager component.

Test the tracking. See Interact with the Example OmniScript and Card.

View the Tracking Data in the Vlocity Tracking Group Page.

View the Vlocity Tracking Entry Records.

Create a Report Using Vlocity Tracking Entry Data.

To enable OmniAnalytics, you must allocate space in the VlocityMetadata partition of the Platform Cache. Then configure custom settings that determine whether OmniAnalytics is enabled and whether data is stored in VlocityTrackingEntry__c object records or both.

Import and Activate the Example OmniScript and FlexCard to help learn about OmniAnalytics.

Create a Tracking Group and Add Components to Track by specifying a group of components to be tracked together.

Create a Lightning App Page with a Tracking Manager that listens for user interaction events and sends data to VlocityTrackingEntry__c objects or both.

Interact with the example OmniScript and FlexCard as if you were an end user to generate tracking data.

View the tracking data in Vlocity Tracking Entry records by creating a custom tab, filtering the list of records, then copying the Data field contents into a JSON formatter.

Create a report using Vlocity Tracking Entry record data and filter it by Vlocity Tracking Group.
title: Configuring OmniAnalytics in Vlocity
